Senator Rabiu Musa Kwankwaso, a former governor of Kano State, says he has yet to decide whether or not to run for president in 2023. In an interview with DW Hausa on Wednesday, Kwankwaso indicated the appropriate persons were being consulted. He said: “In this kind of situation we are not rushing to make decisions. Also Read: Fayemi: Entrenched Interests Within APC Plotting Against Me Over 2023 Elections “So, we are critically watching and consulting the right people to advise us and whatever I decide will be communicated to our people. “We have huge support that is enough to contest for anything. “We have people everywhere not only in Nigeria. Some people think that we only have people in Kano or in the north, but the truth is we have people in Asia, America and Europe,” Kwankwaso said.